<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section section--cream">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="section-heading reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Common Questions</span>
      <h2>Respite Care — FAQs</h2>
    </div>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">How long is a typical respite stay?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Most respite stays are 30 days or longer, though shorter arrangements may be possible depending on availability. We recommend calling us directly to discuss timing and current availability. Our admissions team will give you an honest answer about what we can accommodate.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Does respite care include personal care services?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Yes, if needed. Personal care services (bathing assistance, medication management, mobility support, and so on) are available to respite guests on the same tiered basis as our long-term assisted living residents. If no personal care is needed, the stay is simply all-inclusive community living with meals, wellness, and activities.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Is there nursing on-site during a respite stay?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Yes. Our on-site licensed RN and LPN are available during the day, and 24/7 staffing is in place throughout a respite stay. The same coverage our permanent residents receive. We don&rsquo;t provide a lesser experience for short-term guests.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Can a respite stay transition to a permanent residency?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Yes, and this happens more often than families expect. If a respite guest decides they want to stay permanently, we work with the family to make that transition as smooth as possible. The respite stay essentially functions as a trial period, and many of our current residents found us that way.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Does long-term care insurance cover respite stays?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Many long-term care insurance policies include a respite care benefit, often a set number of days per year. Our admissions team can help you understand your policy and complete any required documentation. Call us and we&rsquo;ll review it together.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

